  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (sufficiency confusion variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Decision rationale incorrectly treats the presence of a validated hemolysis fault-detection threshold (RH < 1 alarm criterion) as the sole and sufficient basis for concluding overall model safety fitness, without addressing model form uncertainty, input sensitivity, or use-error controls.",
